    • Constructor Detail

      • ScalarList

        @Deprecated
public ScalarList()
        Deprecated. Use makeScalarListFromType(FieldType) instead, to instantiate ScalarList objects with an explicit type for the scalar elements of the list.
        Default constructor with an unspecified type for the scalar objects of the list. Consumers of this constructor are responsible to explicitly set the type of the scalar objects of this list by explicitly invoking setScalarType(FieldType).
        Since:
        1.3.0.1

    • Method Detail

      • makeScalarListFromType

        public static ScalarList makeScalarListFromType(FieldType type)
        Factory method to create a ScalarList object with the specified scalar field type. Valid scalar types are: FieldType.INT_TYPE, FieldType.FLOAT_TYPE, FieldType.STRING_TYPE, Text and Span. Any other type will result in a RuntimeException. This is the recommended method of instantiating a ScalarList object.
        Parameters:
        type - Type of the scalar objects of this list
        Returns:
        a list of scalar objects with the input type

      • setScalarType

        public void setScalarType(FieldType type)
        Sets the scalar type for the scalar objects of this list. Valid scalar types are: FieldType.INT_TYPE, FieldType.FLOAT_TYPE, FieldType.STRING_TYPE, Text and Span. Any other type will result in a RuntimeException.
        Parameters:
        type - Type of the elements of this ScalarList
